# 10 : HARDWARE TARGET + ABSTRACTION (v2)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ PRIMARY TARGET (v1 immediate)
  CPU : Intel 12-14-gen (Alder/Raptor/Meteor Lake)
        x86-64 + AVX2 base + AVX-512 opportunistic-runtime-dispatch
  GPU : Intel Arc A770 (Xe-HPG DG2-512) primary
        NVIDIA + AMD via SPIR-V portability
  OS  : Windows + Linux primary, Mac + mobile + browser via §§ 14
  API : Vulkan 1.4.333 primary + Level-Zero secondary-compute (R18)

§ ARC A770 DETAILED SPECS
  architecture : Xe-HPG (Alchemist) DG2-512
  Xe-cores : 32
  per-Xe-core : 16 XVE (256-bit) + 16 XMX + 1 RT-unit
  totals : 512 XVE + 512 XMX + 32 RT-cores
  clock : 2.1 GHz (boost)
  peak-FP32 : 17.2 TFLOPs
  peak-FP16 (XMX) : 137.6 TOPs
  peak-INT8 (XMX) : 275.2 TOPs
  peak-BF16 (XMX) : 137.6 TOPs
  memory : 16 GB GDDR6, 256-bit, 17.5 Gbps, 560 GB/s bandwidth
  L2 : 16 MB
  PCIe : 4.0 × 16
  TDP : 225 W
  display : DP 2.0 UHBR10 + HDMI 2.1

§ XMX MATRIX ENGINE
  Intel-equivalent of NVIDIA Tensor-cores / AMD WMMA
  ops : matmul FP16×FP16 → FP32, BF16×BF16 → FP32, INT8×INT8 → INT32
  SPIR-V access :
    SPV_INTEL_subgroup_matrix_multiply_accumulate
    OR KHR_cooperative_matrix (preferred-portable)
  Level-Zero direct-access (R18) :
    ze_module_cooperative_matrix_capabilities_t
  CSSLv3 effect-tag : {XMX}
  compile-gate : @requires(hw.xmx)
  iGPU-vs-dGPU : KHR_cooperative_matrix NOT exposed on Arrow-Lake iGPU
    ⇒ compile-time feature-query + runtime-fallback

§ RT UNIT
  ops : hw BVH-traversal, TLAS + BLAS + Instance, intersection-shaders
  Vulkan bindings :
    VK_KHR_ray_tracing_pipeline
    VK_KHR_acceleration_structure
    VK_KHR_ray_query (preferred inline-RT)
  params : maxRayRecursionDepth = 256, shaderGroupHandleSize = 32,
           shaderGroupBaseAlignment = 32, maxRayHitAttributeSize = 32
  CSSLv3 effect-tag : {RT}
  compile-gate : @requires(hw.rt)

§ AVX2 + AVX-512 OPPORTUNISTIC
  base : x86-64-v3 ≡ AVX2 + FMA3 + BMI1/2 + LZCNT + MOVBE + POPCNT
  runtime-dispatch :
    comptime emits AVX2 + AVX-512 variants for hot kernels
    startup-probe : CPUID (target-isa-detect stage0 via Cranelift, stage1+ owned)
    fn-pointer table dispatch per-CPU
  pattern : Highway + ISPC
  effect-tags : {SIMD256} (AVX2) | {SIMD512} (AVX-512)

§ VULKAN 1.4 BASELINE (driver 32.0.101.8629 verified on A770)
  core (came-free-in-1.4) :
    VK_KHR_maintenance5 / maintenance6 / maintenance7 / maintenance8
    VK_KHR_dynamic_rendering + dynamic_rendering_local_read
    VK_KHR_push_descriptor
    VK_KHR_shader_subgroup_rotate
    VK_KHR_shader_expect_assume
    VK_KHR_global_priority
    VK_KHR_shader_float_controls2   ← F1-AD numerical-stability critical
    VK_KHR_index_type_uint8
    VK_KHR_line_rasterization
    VK_KHR_vertex_attribute_divisor
  extensions (confirmed-on-A770 driver 8629) :
    VK_KHR_cooperative_matrix (dGPU only)
    VK_KHR_ray_tracing_pipeline / acceleration_structure / ray_query
    VK_EXT_descriptor_indexing (now core in 1.2, used pervasively)
    VK_EXT_mutable_descriptor_type (Arc BDA-bindless workaround)
    VK_KHR_shader_non_semantic_info (debugPrintf inline)
    NonSemantic.Shader.DebugInfo.100 (RenderDoc source-correlation)
  core 1.1-1.3 essentials (carried-forward) :
    PhysicalStorageBuffer64 BDA
    VulkanMemoryModelDeviceScope
    RuntimeDescriptorArray + ShaderNonUniform (bindless)
    GroupNonUniform{Arithmetic, Ballot, Shuffle, Quad}
    Int8/16/64 + Float16/64 + StorageBuffer16BitAccess
    DemoteToHelperInvocation (1.6 core)

§ LEVEL-ZERO BASELINE (R18 • secondary compute-path)
  spec : Level-Zero 1.14+ (public) or latest-available
  host-API :
    ze_driver_handle_t, ze_device_handle_t
    ze_command_list_t (immediate or reusable)
    ze_event_t, ze_event_pool_t (low-latency sync)
    ze_module_t (consumes SPIR-V directly)
    ze_kernel_t
    USM : ze_device_mem_alloc_desc_t, ze_host_mem_alloc_desc_t, shared
  sysman (R18 telemetry-backing) :
    zesPowerSetLimits / zesPowerGetEnergyCounter
    zesTemperatureGetState
    zesFrequencyGetState / zesFrequencyOcGet
    zesDeviceProcessesGetState
    zesEngineGetActivity
    zesRasGetState (reliability/availability/serviceability)
  scope : Intel-only in-practice (spec-portable, no other impls ship)

§ HW-ABSTRACTION via EFFECT-ROW (§§ 04)
  {XMX}         — matrix-engine required
  {RT}          — ray-tracing required
  {SIMD256}     — AVX2
  {SIMD512}     — AVX-512
  {CooperativeMatrix}  — portable matrix-op
  {SubgroupQuad}       — quad-subgroup (derivatives)
  {AtomicFloat}        — OpAtomicFAdd
  {Backend<api>}       — Vulkan | LevelZero | D3D12 | Metal | WebGPU | GNM | NVN
  {Target<platform>}   — Win | Linux | Mac | iOS | Android | PS5 | XboxSeries | Switch2 | Browser
  {Power<mW>} {Thermal<C>} — sysman-backed on Intel (R18)
  {Telemetry<scope>}   — §§ 22
  compile-dispatch :
    target-profile "arc_a770" → XMX + RT + VK-1.4 + L0 caps enabled
    target-profile "generic_vk14" → non-XMX fallback selected
    target-profile "web" → WebGPU subset, no-BDA, no-RT
  ≡ vendor-agnostic surface + vendor-specific lowering

§ PER-VENDOR LOWERING (not-deferred)
  NVIDIA : SPIR-V-portability (no NV-proprietary), CooperativeMatrixKHR preferred
  AMD    : SPIR-V-portability, RDNA3+ WMMA via CooperativeMatrixKHR
  Apple  : Metal-native or MoltenVK (§§ 14 pick-per-target)
  Qualcomm (mobile) : VK-1.3+ via Adreno drivers
  ARM Mali (mobile) : VK-1.3+ via ARM drivers
  WebGPU : Tint-WGSL emit, WebGPU capability-subset

§ DRIVER BUG SURFACE (Intel Arc A770 as-of 2026-Q2)
  BDA + bindless-descriptor-indexing corner-cases :
    workaround — VK_EXT_mutable_descriptor_type where-possible
  BDA synchronization-subtle :
    workaround — explicit VkMemoryBarrier2 (don't rely on memory-model-only)
  some subgroup-shuffle patterns slow-fallback :
    profile-per-release, avoid known-slow SPIR-V patterns
  iGPU-vs-dGPU cooperative-matrix split :
    compile-time feature-query + runtime-fallback
  mitigation :
    CI-matrix : Linux-Mesa-ANV + Windows-Arc-ISV-driver
    differential-testing Vulkan-vs-L0 (§§ 23) catches regressions
    driver-version probed + warn-if-below-known-good

§ SYSMAN AVAILABILITY TABLE
  backend       power   thermal   frequency   engine-util   ras
  Level-Zero    direct  direct    direct      direct        direct
  Vulkan VK_*   partial partial   limited     partial       ✗
  D3D12         DXGI    DXGI      partial     partial       ✗
  Metal         MTLC    limited   limited     MTLC          ✗
  WebGPU        ✗       ✗         ✗           ✗             ✗
  ≡ R18-{Telemetry<full>} requires Level-Zero on Intel for full-fidelity

§ CI REQUIREMENTS
  runners :
    Linux x86-64 + AVX2 (+ optional AVX-512) + Mesa-ANV-Arc-A770
    Windows x86-64 + AVX2 + Intel-Arc-ISV-driver
    Mac x86-64 / ARM64 + Metal-on-Arc-A770 N/A (discrete-only) — iGPU or integrated-Mac-GPU
    browser : headless-Chrome + WebGPU
  test-matrix :
    unit-tests (CPU) : AVX2 + AVX-512 variants
    GPU-smoke : each example rendered + golden-frame compare
    spirv-val : every-emitted-blob (mandatory)
    spirv-cross round-trip : regression-detect
    renderdoc-snapshot : key-frames captured
    differential : Vulkan ↔ Level-Zero same-SPIR-V bit-compare (§§ 23)
    power/thermal-regression : historical-baseline stored per-benchmark

§ FALLBACK HARDWARE (dev-machines)
  min : x86-64-v3 + Vulkan-1.3+ GPU (warn if not-Arc)
  Apocky primary : Intel 12-14-gen + Arc A770
  travel/low-end : integrated-GPU → perf-degraded-but-functional

§ NON-TARGETS (v1 explicit)
  N! direct compute-API without Vulkan-interop (no raw OpenCL path v1)
  N! obsolete-DX (DX11, DX9) — interop via middleware only
  N! OpenGL path (SPIR-V via GL_ARB_gl_spirv possible but not-prioritized)

§ FUTURE-HW (v2+)
  RTX-40/50 portability (should work v1 via SPIR-V)
  RDNA3/4 portability (same)
  Apple-Silicon Metal native
  mobile (Snapdragon, Apple-Silicon, Mali)
  WebGPU browser-LoA
  console-specific (PS5 GNM, Xbox D3D12X, Switch-2 NVN) via §§ 14 stubs

